{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015i6xvdUofXR1PEQbCUBr7c","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tA Spark cluster and data skew benchmark job have been deployed, but there are\n2\tconfiguration issues that need to be fixed before the jobs can run successfully.\n3\t\n4\tYOUR TASK:\n5\t1. Diagnose and fix the configuration bugs in the deployment\n6\t2. Apply optimization strategies to fix the data skew problem\n7\t3. Compare performance across different strategies\n8\t\n9\tPROBLEM DESCRIPTION:\n10\t- Dataset: orders (large), products (small), customers (medium)\n11\t- Join on product_id has severe data skew\n12\t- 5 hot products (product_id 1-5) receive 50% of all orders\n13\t- This causes some partitions to be 10x larger than others\n14\t- Result: Slow query performance due to stragglers\n15\t\n16\tSTEP 1: DIAGNOSE AND FIX CLUSTER/JOB ISSUES\n17\tThe initial deployment has bugs that prevent jobs from running.\n18\tCheck the status and logs to identify and fix the issues.\n19\t\n20\t```bash\n21\t# Check cluster and job status\n22\tkubectl get pods -n spark-skew\n23\tkubectl get jobs -n spark-skew\n24\t\n25\t# Check Spark master logs for startup issues\n26\tkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l app=spark-master\n27\t\n28\t# Check baseline job logs for errors\n29\tkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline\n30\t```\n31\t\n32\tSTEP 2: ONCE FIXED - OBSERVE THE BASELINE\n33\t```bash\n34\t# Check baseline job status\n35\tkubectl get job spark-skew-baseline -n spark-skew\n36\t\n37\t# Watch baseline job logs - observe the skew ratio and slow performance\n38\tkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline -f\n39\t```\n40\t\n41\tSTEP 3: APPLY BROADCAST JOIN OPTIMIZATION\n42\t```bash\n43\t# Apply the broadcast join job (may need fixes too)\n44\tkubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_data_skew/resource/skew-job-broadcast.yaml\n45\t\n46\t# Watch the broadcast job - should be faster!\n47\tkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=broadcast -f\n48\t```\n49\t\n50\tSTEP 4: APPLY AQE OPTIMIZATION\n51\t```bash\n52\t# Apply the AQE (Adaptive Query Execution) job\n53\tkubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_data_skew/resource/skew-job-aqe.yaml\n54\t\n55\t# Watch the AQE job - Spark auto-handles skew\n56\tkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=aqe -f\n57\t```\n58\t\n59\tSTEP 5: COMPARE RESULTS\n60\t```bash\n61\t# Check all jobs completed\n62\tkubectl get jobs -n spark-skew\n63\t\n64\t# View all job logs to compare performance\n65\tkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline --tail=20\n66\tkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=broadcast --tail=20\n67\tkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=aqe --tail=20\n68\t```\n69\t\n70\tSUCCESS CRITERIA:\n71\t- All configuration bugs fixed\n72\t- Baseline job completed successfully (shows slow performance)\n73\t- At least ONE optimization strategy applied (broadcast or aqe)\n74\t- Optimization shows performance improvement vs baseline\n75\t- All applied jobs completed successfully"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f8e8a8f-3fbb-456c-87a3-3abb0d2e573b","uuid":"4bf27229-b44a-4ce0-96cd-469ca7666526","timestamp":"2026-06-23T17:45:29.932Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/runs/long-rererun/spark-long-pipeline-buildout-20260623_170901/stages/stage_08/prompt.txt","content":"A Spark cluster and data skew benchmark job have been deployed, but there are\nconfiguration issues that need to be fixed before the jobs can run successfully.\n\nYOUR TASK:\n1. Diagnose and fix the configuration bugs in the deployment\n2. Apply optimization strategies to fix the data skew problem\n3. Compare performance across different strategies\n\nPROBLEM DESCRIPTION:\n- Dataset: orders (large), products (small), customers (medium)\n- Join on product_id has severe data skew\n- 5 hot products (product_id 1-5) receive 50% of all orders\n- This causes some partitions to be 10x larger than others\n- Result: Slow query performance due to stragglers\n\nSTEP 1: DIAGNOSE AND FIX CLUSTER/JOB ISSUES\nThe initial deployment has bugs that prevent jobs from running.\nCheck the status and logs to identify and fix the issues.\n\n```bash\n# Check cluster and job status\nkubectl get pods -n spark-skew\nkubectl get jobs -n spark-skew\n\n# Check Spark master logs for startup issues\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l app=spark-master\n\n# Check baseline job logs for errors\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline\n```\n\nSTEP 2: ONCE FIXED - OBSERVE THE BASELINE\n```bash\n# Check baseline job status\nkubectl get job spark-skew-baseline -n spark-skew\n\n# Watch baseline job logs - observe the skew ratio and slow performance\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline -f\n```\n\nSTEP 3: APPLY BROADCAST JOIN OPTIMIZATION\n```bash\n# Apply the broadcast join job (may need fixes too)\nkubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_data_skew/resource/skew-job-broadcast.yaml\n\n# Watch the broadcast job - should be faster!\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=broadcast -f\n```\n\nSTEP 4: APPLY AQE OPTIMIZATION\n```bash\n# Apply the AQE (Adaptive Query Execution) job\nkubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_data_skew/resource/skew-job-aqe.yaml\n\n# Watch the AQE job - Spark auto-handles skew\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=aqe -f\n```\n\nSTEP 5: COMPARE RESULTS\n```bash\n# Check all jobs completed\nkubectl get jobs -n spark-skew\n\n# View all job logs to compare performance\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline --tail=20\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=broadcast --tail=20\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=aqe --tail=20\n```\n\nSUCCESS CRITERIA:\n- All configuration bugs fixed\n- Baseline job completed successfully (shows slow performance)\n- At least ONE optimization strategy applied (broadcast or aqe)\n- Optimization shows performance improvement vs baseline\n- All applied jobs completed successfully","numLines":75,"startLine":1,"totalLines":75}}}
